    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>To display number of count for taxonomy terms in views block (Drupal 7), you can do the following -</p>
<p>1. Create a views block<br />
2. Under fields,  add taxonomy term: Name<br />
4. Under relationships, add taxonomy terms: content with term<br />
5. Under contextual filter, add taxonomy term: name, choose "Display a summary", "Display record count with link". </p>
<p>You will have views block which will display taxonomy terms with number count for example -</p>
<p>cows (2)<br />
dog (3)<br />
cats (7)</p></div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-tags field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-above clearfix"><h3 class="field-label">Tags: </h3><ul class="links"><li class="taxonomy-term-reference-0" rel="dc:subject"><a href="/taxonomy/term/2" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype="">taxonomy terms</a></li><li class="taxonomy-term-reference-1" rel="dc:subject"><a href="/taxonomy/term/3" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype="">count</a></li><li class="taxonomy-term-reference-2" rel="dc:subject"><a href="/taxonomy/term/4" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype="">Drupal</a></li><li class="taxonomy-term-reference-3" rel="dc:subject"><a href="/taxonomy/term/5" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype="">views</a></li></ul></div>
